Reviews: Looks to be doing it's job so far
I have always sprayed my azaleas rhododendrons and camelias with a soluble fertilizer, but Miracle Gro seems to have a better NPK ratio, and the plants are flowering better this year than before
Wow, this stuff works, my palm-trees have a lot of new growth and look very healthy ðŸ˜ƒ
Easy to use, and gets results.

This is an amazing product which produces more flowers, greener leaves and is so simple to use. I am not a gardener but I would not be without this product in my garden shed as it gives amazing results time after time.

I used it this past spring and can confidently say that it made my plants look bigger and livelier than before. Yes it doesn't look like the most natural fertiliser and it won't improve your overall soil quality but it definitely delivers the nutrients and food that plants need. It's so simple I usually just mix two spoons to a 9L watering can and just give the plants a good feed every 2 or so weeks. It's definitely a quick solution for plants that aren't looking that great or just need a quick boost. I won't solely rely on this as I believe plants do need some compost or organic matter to improve overall soil quality as well but this is great when I don't have much time to garden.

Plants love it and take off! I've had to prune more often andvI have so many more lemons on my potted plants, I'm giving them to friends. I've been using this product for 20+ years and still use the original sprayer. Didn't use for last 5 years, it wasn't available in my area, until I saw it on Amazon, and I order heaps at a time.
Proven product easy to use.
